>> time required: 55 minutes
>> image: https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/30/2020/08/cauliflower-paneer-pea-curry-eb0eb5d.jpg?resize=768,574

Heat 1 @tbsp{2} of @oil{2%tbsp} in a large non-stick frying pan, add the @paneer{225%g} and fry gently until crisp. Remove with a slotted spoon and set aside. Add the remaining oil and the @cauliflower{1%head} to the pan, and cook for ~{10%min}s until browned. Add the @onions{2}, and a little more oil if needed, and cook for a further ~{5%min}s until softened. Stir in the @garlic{2%clove} and curry paste, then pour in the @passata{500%g} and 250ml water, and season. Bring to a simmer, then cover and cook for ~{18-20%min}s or until the cauliflower is just tender.

Add the @frozen peas{200%g} and crispy paneer to the pan and cook for a further ~{5%min}s. Stir through most of the @coriander{0%small} and garnish with the rest. Serve with @basmati rice or naan{} bread, @raita or your favourite chutney{}.
